The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a method for boosting domain adaptation performance by leveraging disentanglement analysis. This involves separating the common and domain-specific features of both domains, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
